sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1630
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: tet R coding sequence combined with mioC promoter to allow production of tet R protein during cell replication.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: kun zhang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M0051
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This sequence codes for the amino acid sequence AANDENYNYADAS, a variation of the WT SsrA tag sequence, which, when fused to the C-terminal of proteins, will make the protein susceptible to fast degradation through SspB-mediated binding to the ClpX protease. The following rates of degradation of this tag are pulled from the corresponding references below: ~2 Vmax/ [Clpx6] min-1 from (1).
See the following references for further information on degradation rates and mechanisms of this tag: (1)McGinness, Baker, Sauer. 2006. Mol. Cell. 22:701. (2)Flynn et al 2003. Mol. Cell. 11: 671. Flynn et al. 2001. PNAS 98(19): 10584. Anderson et al 1998. App. Env. Microbiol. 64(6):2240.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Felix Moser
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This variation of the SsrA tag was studied by McGinness, Baker, Sauer. 2006. Mol. Cell. 22:701.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
C-terminal tag. Degradation rate is fast. Variations of this sequence yield different degradation rates(see Parts BBa_M0050, BBa_M0052, BBa_M0053). Sequence derived from reverse translation of AANDENYNYADAS sequence using codon usage optimized for E. coli. Three C-terminal aa's (DAS in this case) are necessary and sufficient for ClpX binding and degradation. Upstream aa sequence serves as a binding site for SspB, which guides rapid binding to ClpX. See sources on the main part page for further information about the mechanism of the system.
NOTE: this sequence has only the amino acid sequence for the tag and bears NO STOP CODONS, so be sure to inlclude them if you use this sequence.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K313002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Flpe is a site-specific DNA recombinase that that recognizes FRT sequence. Flpe was derived from yeaset site-specific DNA recombinase Flp. (Buchholz, et al.,Improved properties of FLP recombinase evolved by cycling mutagenesis. Nature. Biotechnology, 16:657-662 ( 1998 ))
It's internal EcoRI and SpeI site has been removed using site-directed mutagenesis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kohaku So, Takashi Hiroi, Megumi Iseki, Mami Nakatake, Ryosuke Kamei, Ryo Kariyazono
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It's internal EcoRI and SpeI site has been removed using site-directed mutagenesis.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: p(tetR)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Sequence for pTet inverting regulator driven by the TetR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: June Rhee, Connie Tao, Ty Thomson, Louis Waldman
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Lutz, R., Bujard, H., Nucleic Acids Research (1997) 25, 1203-1210.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: BBa_R0040 TetR-Regulated Promoter is based on a cI promoter. It has been modified to include two TetR binding sites and the BioBrick standard assembly head and tail restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: FRT
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Site for recombination by flp recombinase. Genes flanked by FRT sites (oriented in the same direction) in the genome can be excised with the introduction of flp recombinase-expressing helper plasmid pCP20. Note that the original FRT sequence contained an XbaI site that has been removed with a point mutation for compatibility with standard assembly. See Datsenko and Wanner for details of its use in markerless knockouts and knockins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: John Anderson
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:

Product is pSB1A2-Bca1010

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: Pu
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the promoter activated by the transcriptional regulator XylR (BBa_I723136) in response to detection of environmental xylene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Scott Ramsay
